    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Allowing the location manager to pause updates can improve battery life on the target device without sacrificing location data. When this property is set to "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/objectivec/yes"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", the location manager pauses updates (and powers down the appropriate hardware) at times when the location data is unlikely to change. For example, if the user stops for food while using a navigation app, the location manager might pause updates for a period of time. You can help the determination of when to pause location updates by assigning a value to the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corelocation/cllocationmanager/1620567-activitytype"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "After a pause occurs, it is your responsibility to restart location services again when you determine that they are needed. Core Location calls the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corelocation/cllocationmanagerdelegate/1621553-locationmanagerdidpauselocationu"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method of your location manager's delegate to let you know that a pause has occurred. In that method, you might configure a local notification whose trigger is of type "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/usernotifications/unlocationnotificationtrigger"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and is set to notify when the user exits the current region. The message for the local notification should prompt the user to launch your app again so that it can resume updates."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "For apps that have in-use authorization, a pause to location updates ends access to location changes until the app is launched again and able to restart those updates. If you do not wish location updates to stop entirely, consider disabling this property and changing location accuracy to "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/corelocation/kcllocationaccuracythreekilometers"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " when your app moves to the background. Doing so allows you to continue receiving location updates in a power-friendly manner. "
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "important"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The default value of this property is "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/objectivec/yes"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". "
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
